The article discusses the Iranian regime's role as the leading state sponsor of terror and its support for terrorist organizations such as Hezbollah and Hamas. It also highlights Iran's funding, arming, and training of militants in the Middle East, as well as its support for the Syrian regime and its human rights abuses within Iran. The article emphasizes the US government's strategy to counter these activities, including cutting off money flows to terrorists and supporting Iranian citizens who demand change. It criticizes the previous administration's policies, particularly the Iran nuclear deal, and outlines the current administration's stance on the deal. The article calls for bipartisan legislation that addresses Iran's nuclear program, missile development, and human rights abuses, and urges other nations to take stronger steps against Iran's malign activities. It also warns that the US will not waive sanctions if an agreement to fix the flaws of the nuclear deal is not reached and threatens to terminate the deal.